    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nRecently I made [a PoC config](https://github.com/boltlessengineer/NativeVim] to see how far can I do with Neovim without any plugins.\nAs a result, I noticed that only missing feature in Neovim compared to other text editors is fuzzy finder like Telescope or fzf-lua.\n\nI understand it is reasonable to give third-party plugins to do the job instead.\nI'm not saying we should put `telescope.nvim` to core. I'm thinking minimized version as a QoL feature.\n\nNeovim recently included features like snippets and commenting. Both were done by third-party plugins before.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI'd like to see a version that is closely tied to the core like [zed](https://zed.dev)'s [multibuffers](https://zed.dev/docs/multibuffers) rather than being a separate feature, but porting `fzf.vim` to builtin plugin can be enough.",
