            "body": "> like [zed](https://zed.dev)'s [multibuffers](https://zed.dev/docs/multibuffers)\n\nmultibuffers are cool and something I see a lot of value in, kind of the inverse of emacs's [NrrwRgn](https://github.com/chrisbra/NrrwRgn). Being able to \"stitch together\" many buffers into 1 virtual buffer is a very powerful idea. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30463#issuecomment-2366605922\n\n\n\n> see [#31745 (comment)](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31745#issuecomment-2564383401)\n\nYep, as mentioned there, a relatively much-lower-cost, extremely high-leverage step is to first ship a minimal plugin manager.",
